{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b0ed5389-b5c7-4a1c-bbe7-cf5b8cef38ba","agentId":"ac3f03fc6222f516b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"\n## Task\nCreate a test list for Conway's Game of Life kata.\n\n## Specification\nImplement Conway's Game of Life with an infinite grid (sparse representation, only store living cells).\n\nRules:\n1. Underpopulation: Any live cell with fewer than 2 live neighbors dies\n2. Survival: Any live cell with 2 or 3 live neighbors lives on\n3. Overpopulation: Any live cell with more than 3 live neighbors dies\n4. Reproduction: Any dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive\n\nThe implementation should accept an arbitrary grid of living cells and output the next generation.\n- Grid is infinite in all directions (positive and negative x/y)\n- Only track living cells (sparse representation)\n- Cells are identified by coordinates (x, y)\n\n## Expected Files\n- Test file: `src/game-of-life.spec.ts`\n- Implementation file: `src/game-of-life.ts`\n\n## Technical Setup\n- TypeScript with Vitest\n- Spec files use `.spec.ts` extension\n- Local module imports use explicit extensions (e.g., `./game-of-life.js`)\n- Tests use `describe`, `it`, `expect` from Vitest\n- Run tests with `pnpm test`\n\n## Important\nThe test list should come from the kata's specification. Do not add generic \"validate input types\" or \"edge cases\" tests unless the spec calls for them.\n\nCreate the test file at `src/game-of-life.spec.ts` with `it.todo()` entries for each test.\nAlso create a minimal `src/game-of-life.ts` implementation file that just exports the function signature (so imports work).\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, no human approval needed.\n"},"uuid":"0f894cd9-9dde-47cf-b1a4-053fed65f9d8","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:09:52.284Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-11_02-09-20_game-of-life-example-mapping_v4.1-minimized_opus-4-6-portkey-2","sessionId":"66